MESSAGE.value: Making ThresholdHeuristic much more aggressive, running with a huge pool of workers, seeing what happens.
Added cacheing, stubbed out MCTS, etc
Lookahead one heuristic seems to work well, if horrendously slowly.
Adding non-stupid NER features. Still need lemmas.
Put in a logistic external model stream, piped both sentiment and person id to it. Still needs an actual model.
Slight refactoring
Getting LogisticRegression working for person and sentiment.
Have an EM system in, with a baby standalone test, though I'm not sure exactly what behavior to expect, so I can't tell if it's totally working.
Online EM implemented, but with bogus gradients...
Online EM seems now to be fixed!!!!! And there was much rejoicing.
Reworked EM to be a less redundant implementation, by adding some horrible type hacks.
Reduced payment by a factor of 4 per example, also added better per example logging.
Fixing up NQuestion baseline to make ordering suck less, also prepping to launch a huge number of tasks.
Have a sampling look-ahead one gameplayer in. This seems to work, though the loss function is a very important variable to tune.
Adding some magic regularization, word vectors, removing strict interpretation from JS code
Running the whole lineup of dirty tricks during rough by-hand gridsearch over hyperparameters. Feels like deep learning.
Now handles doing reasonable analysis, records historical f1, and machine only f1, so we can see how we're doing.
Removing legend from my beautiful plots.
Got numbers graphing against the dev set, so analysis can proceed properly.
Think I fixed the broken learning loss plots problem. ALL OF THE PLOTS!!!!
Added a test for Logistic regression. It's a shit test, so will have to copy Dan Klein's traffic lights eventually.
Added a bunch of logic to timeout inactive workers, and deal with AFK punters.
Got the sentiment and face recognition datasets working well.
Getting the tasks working better, person id and sentiment. Person ID seems to have a runaway confidence problem. Need to add observation count filtering, if I don't already have it.
Have discovered a mysterious deadlock in the multiclass use case someplace. Will have to explore.
